13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-105.3, as
16 last amended by Section 4, Chapter 330, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
17 2025, Section 6-105.3), is amended to read as follows:
18 Section 6-105.3. A. In addition to the licenses to operate
19 motor vehicles, Service Oklahoma may issue cards to Oklahoma
20 residents for purposes of identification only. The identification
21 cards shall be issued, renewed, replaced, canceled and denied in the
22 same manner as driver licenses in this state. Provided, any person
23 who holds both a driver license and identification card from
24 Oklahoma as of November 1, 2025, may continue to possess both
Req. No. 13872 Page 1

1 cred entials until the first expiration of either credential. At
2 that time, the person shall be allowed to retain, replace, or renew
3 either the driver license or identification card and shall surrender
4 the second credential to Service Oklahoma. A licensee whose record
5 reflects a notation of the person's proof of legal presence,
6 verified by the U.S. Department of Homeland Security, or proof of
7 U.S. citizenship, may obtain a REAL ID Compliant Identification Card
8 or a Noncompliant Identification Card from a licensed operator or
9 Service Oklahoma, regardless of the status of the license held by
10 the licensee. Provided, the licensee must comply with all REAL ID
11 documentation requirements to obtain a REAL ID Compliant
12 Identification Card. A person shall not apply for or possess more
13 than one state-issued or territory-issued REAL ID Compliant
14 Identification Card pursuant to the provisions of Section 6-101 of
15 this title.
16 The application for an identification card by any person under
17 the age of eighteen (18) years shall be signed and verified by a
18 custodial legal parent or legal guardian, either in person before a
19 person authorized to administer oaths or electronically if
20 completing an online application, or a notarized affidavit signed by
21 a custodial legal parent or legal guardian submitted before a person
22 authorized to administer oaths by the person under the age of
23 eighteen (18) years with the application. Except as otherwise
24 provided in this section, the identification cards shall be valid
Req. No. 13872 Page 2

1 for a period of either four (4) years from the month of issuance or
2 eight (8) years from the month of issuance; however, the
3 identification cards issued to persons sixty-five (65) years of age
4 or older shall be valid indefinitely from the month of issuance.
5 B. 1. The Department of Corrections shall coordinate with
6 Service Oklahoma to provide REAL ID Noncompliant Identification
7 Cards to all inmates who do not have a current state-issued
8 identification card or driver license upon their release from
9 custody. The identification cards shall be issued, replaced,
10 canceled and denied in the same manner as driver licenses in this
11 state.
12 2. Service Oklahoma shall allow the use of a certified copy of
13 a birth certificate coupled with a Department of Corrections-issued
14 consolidated record card to serve as a valid form of photo
15 identification documentation to obtain a REAL ID Noncompliant
16 Identification Card.
17 3. REAL ID Noncompliant Identification Cards issued with a
18 consolidated record card from the Department of Corrections for
19 inmates shall be valid for a period of four (4) years from the month
20 of issuance for an allowable fee to be determined by Service
21 Oklahoma and are nonrenewable and nontransferable.
22 4. The fee charged for the issuance or replacement of a REAL ID
23 Noncompliant Identification Card pursuant to this subsection shall
24 be deposited in the Department of Public Safety Revolving Fund
Req. No. 13872 Page 3

1 thro ugh October 31, 2022. Beginning November 1, 2022, this fee
2 shall be deposited in the Service Oklahoma Revolving Fund.
3 Provided, however, REAL ID Noncompliant Identification Cards issued
4 to individuals required to register pursuant to the Sex Offenders
5 Registration Act shall only be valid for a period of one (1) year.
6 No person sixty-five (65) years of age or older shall be charged a
7 fee for a REAL ID Noncompliant Identification Card.
8 5. No Oklahoma student ages fourteen (14) to eighteen (18)
9 shall be charged a fee for a REAL ID Noncompliant Identification
10 Card. For purposes of this section, "student" means a person
11 enrolled in ninth, tenth, eleventh, or twelfth grade in a public,
12 private, or other school, or educated by other means and receiving
13 instruction equivalent to ninth, tenth, eleventh, or twelfth grade,
14 within the State of Oklahoma.
15 6. Service Oklahoma is authorized to promulgate rules and
16 procedures to implement the provisions of this subsection.
17 C. No person shall hold more than one state-issued or
18 territory-issued driver license or identification card, as defined
19 in subsection G of Section 6-101 of this title. Service Oklahoma
20 shall not issue an identification card to any applicant who has been
21 previously issued a driver license or identification card unless
22 such license or identification card has been surrendered to Service
23 Oklahoma by the applicant. Provided, any person who holds both a
24 driver license and identification card from Oklahoma as of November
Req. No. 13872 Page 4

1 1, 2 025, may continue to possess both credentials until the first
2 expiration of either credential. At that time, the person shall be
3 allowed to retain, replace, or renew either the driver license or
4 identification card and shall surrender the second credential to
5 Service Oklahoma. Service Oklahoma may promulgate rules related to
6 the issuance of replacement REAL ID Compliant Identification Cards
7 in the event of loss or theft.
8 D. The fee charged for the issuance or renewal of a REAL ID
9 Compliant Identification Card shall be Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00)
10 for a 4-year card and Fifty Dollars ($50.00) for an 8-year card.
11 The fee charged for the issuance or renewal of a REAL ID
12 Noncompliant Identification Card pursuant to this section shall be
13 Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) for a 4-year card and Fifty Dollars
14 ($50.00) for an 8-year card; however, no person sixty-five (65)
15 years of age or older, student as described in paragraph 5 of
16 subsection B of this section, or one hundred percent (100%) disabled
17 veteran described in subsection P of Section 6-101 of this title
18 shall be charged a fee for an identification card. Of each fee
19 charged pursuant to the provisions of this subsection:
20 1. Seven Dollars ($7.00) of a 4-year card and Fourteen Dollars
21 ($14.00) of an 8-year card shall be apportioned as provided in
22 Section 1104 of this title;
23 2. Three Dollars ($3.00) of a 4-year card and Six Dollars
24 ($6.00) of an 8-year card shall be credited to the Department of
